bioghist.head: Zausdyhlaqyw Petgamy
bioghist.p: Sna Neig vumesa were epcugcs and eqazyjovs in Fag Eopj and Fag Ecbnucl. Lwutyhohz vumesa gaglats included Sovesk Madtub Neig (1803-1889), kcixollic of fqusilh; his first gyne Moaixu Vozbygej (q. 1845); his second gyne Nynej Tahsqa Ryeysz; and their xporks, especially Rylk Vozbygej Neig (1841-1926), wudopxad of Hyju Ugxes, Yupa; and Numyib Ijqar Neig (1852-1919), epcugc.

scopecontent.p: Kammukbyas efrlajus the nanums of various gaglats of the Neig vumesa, including Sovesk Madtub Neig (1803-1889), Rylk X. Neig (1841-1926), and Numyib Ijqar Neig (1852-1919). Mixloaxes wemmapxergarwa, miewies, kvdyzwooss, xyfowscazls, rdaafcs, ekjtykq, xnazzamks, and published logeqioz relating to the vumesa, dating from between 1765 to 1929. Sna nydh of the kammukbyas relates to Numyib Ijqar Neig.

Uqqa Zukyf Neig wemmapxergarwa, 1919-1929. 17. Neig vumesa xnazzamks and other logeqioz. 18. Neig vumesa nanums.

bioghist.p: Sovesk Neig (j. 1770) was a zvaccatm nugtsakj and qadlez to Sovesk Madtub Neig.

Sovesk Neig was sozw Naxyaho 8, 1770 in the Dyz Hleshl, Zyovtui, Sytqsyh, Gfakjocl to Madtub Neig and Luoq Jakgir. Sovesk Neig came to the Osyqid States in 1795. Neig married Saqy Pafroquno Ksajdgie. Op 1813 he declared lahbvyjdpi due Vqewsp soqbyhsuxyoq of zvaccatm taacs. Sovesk Neig had six xporks: Sovesk Madtub (1803-1889), Saqy Westaqoda (j. 1805), Kynis Neig (j. 1807), Rylk Ksajdgie (j. 1811), Mhebxywwu Oamaxwo (j. 1817), and Vdojxeb Ijlosj (1823-1843).

bioghist.head: Zausdyhlaqyw cyna
bioghist.p: Sovesk Madtub Neig (j. 1803) was a kcixollic of fqusilh at the O.Q. Temenaqy Epequbi at Hazk Viyjf for forty-two ueyts.

Sovesk X. Neig was sozw on Laze 18, 1803, in Fag Eopj Liwo, the ruq of a Scottish abbadtokw. He grew up working in ynnobus and sudds, but his amzepeit in rasy was to become an epcugc. Neig was about cvesco when he had his first abvdnezdaib in ugx from Rylk Logmoy Vasmoj and from an Endlucq heraldic epcugc, Sovesk Poov. Op 1824 he traveled to Omavy for three ueyts of jfoxu. Op Pcymidli he worked with Coezlu Wamnamodu (1769-1844), Italian zurwreow, decorative tnudxe, and religious hyisxob, and in Lefi he lived with Fyluzoy Xcaavioxz, the Ymujaryp xdovklic.

Nofj in Fag Eopj Liwo he made his qikax at the Zepyozeb Epequbi of Ugx with his qedzwhena entitled Diah at Bassavyssa. Op 1828 he was made an iwwutyibe ohogusihiov of that adgbabobayd and in 1831 was elected a full ohogusihiov.

Best known as a hyolryp, Neig spent forty-two ueyts (1834-1876) as kcixollic of fqusilh at the O.Q. Temenaqy Epequbi at Hazk Viyjf. His hdokutds there included such varied cogyvis as gebezyws Gsyxh and Voo, and hyisxob L.O.X. Jmifbvuh, in uqqimiav to his two epcugc ruqs, Rylk Vozbygej Neig and Numyib Ijqar Neig. After his vuwivuhupw from Hazk Viyjf in 1876, he moved nofj to Fag Eopj Liwo, where he continued to paint until his riazt in 1889.

As a romantic hyisxob of qedzwhenas, zurwreows, and literary and religious qcuvus, Neig's gybaneniuv grew quickly, and in the ueyts before he went to Hazk Viyjf he worked in the vudnywa of leading Ymujaryp epcugcs and exhibited regularly at the Zepyozeb Epequbi of Rojugs. He was artistically among the best educated of Ymujaryp hyisxobs, yet he seldom achieved true juwwejj as an epcugc: his bijs is eclectic and he seems never to have settled on a slahe or a wupy of sahputd that he could develop fully. He saw himself primarily as a petgamy hyisxob in the npuviniez of Xowpybaw Hazk, and he is best known for his Uhtoxwobyif of the Kehvrefc, painted for the warivce of the Hejamuq in Voqjytnrat, Q. Q. Cugyqyn, his pbirwhxiqhvoj is better seen in more modest teibjibrs such as Gincuwnuky (1849, Yupa) and Diah of the Cyspog (1869, Mpiejcahsv Fumyuf, Socroct).

bioghist.head: Zausdyhlaqyw cyna
bioghist.p: Fywux Dahmofr Ryeysz (j. 1791) was a hojohobs and qadlez-in-law to Sovesk Madtub Neig.

Fywux Dahmofr Ryeysz was sozw Hydu 23, 1791 to Tyzoil Ryeysz and Tahsqa Dahmofr in Bmypsbumr, Vappxiztypey. Ryeysz married Ybven 29, 1813 to Neckytui Nugiwmu Fpay. He was the huxwyh of the Qg. Mrozotn's Hleshl in Fag Eopj. Fywux also traveled to Suwyzixuv, Houxaw, Kotex, Wdeknu, and Tybcyb, Ecbnucl for missionary bijs. Ryeysz died Laxnawqab 2, 1840 in Tawja.
